
Automake converts a → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System/Makefile_am into a → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System/Makefile_in.

The goal is to create portable makefiles.

Automake is written in → development/languages/Perl/.

Automake is used in tandem with → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System/Autoconf.

Automake consists of the following two commands:
  • aclocal
  • automake

sa:
  → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System[GNU Build System]
